<a name="BST04.2">
 <h3 style="text-align: center">
 Course configuration with examples and tests
 </h3>
<h4 style="text-align: center">F. Bagnoli, A.Sterbini and M.Temperini</h4>
<h4 style="text-align: center">ABSTRACT</h4>
<p style="text-align: center">
We show the recent developments for an existing logical
framework for course configuration. The framework allows
the selection of learning components collected in a didactic
pool, to configure a course over the needs of the learner. A
knowledge item is a notion, that can be necessary to study a
certain component, or that is acquired through it. The defi-
nition of learning components is enriched with the concepts
of example knowledge item and test knowledge item. This allows
the definition of distinct learning resources, which can
cooperate in teaching the same related knowledge item, yet
with different aims (such as to deliver the plain notion, or make
additional examples, or test the learner’s knowledge about that
concept). Aspects related to the optimization of configured
course (so to have limited and better distribution of learning
effort, during the course) are also discussed.
</p>

