<a name="ST03.2">
 <h3 style="text-align: center">
 The Design and Implementation of a Logical Framework for Course
 Configuration in eLearning
 </h3>
<h4 style="text-align: center">A.Sterbini and M.Temperini</h4>
<h4 style="text-align: center">ABSTRACT</h4>
<p style="text-align: center">
A logical framework for the definition of courses tailored over the
individual needs of different learners is presented.
This framework describes, by means of propositional logic, how to
specify knowledge relationships among the {\em didactic components}
that are present in a {\em didactic pool}, so that the outcoming
course will meet the needs of each individual student.
Moreover, the framework describes how to specify the {\em target
  knowledge} taught by the course and also the {\em starting
  knowledge} that the student possesses at the beginning.
It describes also how to use the specifications to choose the set of
components needed and how these components have to be sequenced in the
produced course.
An initial implementation in Prolog of the framework is currently
under construction.
Samples of its use are given.
</p>

