<A NAME="CiCoTe-IASI-96b">
<CENTER><h3>AN APPROACH TO CLASS REASONING IN SYMBOLIC COMPUTATION</h3>
<h4>Gianna Cioni, Attilio Colagrossi and  Marco Temperini</h4></CENTER>

<CENTER><h4>ABSTRACT</h4>
</CENTER>
We present a methodology that follows the object-oriented paradigm
in order to allow for modeling mathematical structures by axiomatization.
<br>
A suitable programming language is defined in terms of its class
construct and inheritance.
<br>
The class construct allows for expressing also the properties of the
structure represented by the class.
<br>
By reasoning about the properties defined in classes ("class reasoning"),
logical relations holding among the related mathematical structures can be
evaluated.
<br>
We show how class reasoning can be applied, in order to rearrange and/or
modify a hierarchy of (classes representing) mathematical structures.
