<A NAME="DiBTe-IASI-95">
<CENTER><h3>$\lambda$\&ESI-CALCULUS FOR ENHANCED STRICT INHERITANCE</STRONG>,
<h4>P. Di Blasio and M. Temperini</h4></CENTER>

<CENTER><h4>ABSTRACT</h4>
</CENTER>
We present a specialization inheritance mechanism for a strongly
typed object-oriented language, called Enhanced Strict Inheritance (ESI).
 It is a mechanism of classification in which the subclassing relation
between classes reflects the subtyping relationship between the
corresponding types.
 The definition of ESI is based on a covariant redefinition rule for
methods.
 ESI is modeled via the lambda&ESI-calculus, a modification
of the lambda&-calculus of overloaded functions due to
Castagna, Ghelli and Longo.
 In ESI hierarchies the only constraint to attribute redefinition
is covariance; any other restriction in redefinition rule and
compatibility of result types in confusable methods is relaxed.
 The ESI approach to method lookup is based on a peculiar notion of
point of view for multiple inheritance, called "abstraction level":
it drives the method lookup and possibly allow to avoid conflict
problems.
